1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:01,742
Most traders lose money.

2
00:00:01,742 --> 00:00:02,512
Not some.

3
00:00:02,512 --> 00:00:03,152
Most.

4
00:00:03,152 --> 00:00:08,282
Studies show around 70 to 80 percent of retail traders end up in the red.

5
00:00:08,282 --> 00:00:12,294
But here's the thing nobody talks about — losing money isn't the bottom of the

6
00:00:12,294 --> 00:00:12,823
ladder.

7
00:00:12,823 --> 00:00:14,871
There are actually levels below that.

8
00:00:14,871 --> 00:00:16,039
And the scary part?

9
00:00:16,039 --> 00:00:19,780
Most people never even realize which level they're on.

10
00:00:19,780 --> 00:00:23,561
we're mapping out every level of trading skill — from the person who just

11
00:00:23,561 --> 00:00:27,257
downloaded Robinhood because their coworker mentioned GameStop,

12
00:00:27,257 --> 00:00:31,507
all the way to the rare operators running systematic strategies that generate

13
00:00:31,507 --> 00:00:34,276
returns regardless of what the market does.

14
00:00:34,276 --> 00:00:36,584
Each level has its own blind spots.

15
00:00:36,584 --> 00:00:38,326
Its own psychology.

16
00:00:38,326 --> 00:00:41,151
Its own relationship with risk and money.

17
00:00:41,151 --> 00:00:42,615
And most importantly,

18
00:00:42,615 --> 00:00:47,377
its own version of the same core mistake — just dressed up differently.

19
00:00:47,377 --> 00:00:50,878
The goal isn't to make you feel good or bad about where you are.

20
00:00:50,878 --> 00:00:55,777
The goal is to show you exactly where you stand, what the next level looks like,

21
00:00:55,777 --> 00:00:58,850
and what it actually takes to get there.

22
00:00:59,472 --> 00:01:03,792
Because the path from Level 1 to Level 5 isn't about finding a better strategy.

23
00:01:03,792 --> 00:01:06,725
It's about a complete rewiring of how you think.

24
00:01:06,725 --> 00:01:09,203
Let's get into it.

25
00:01:09,203 --> 00:01:11,065
1 is where almost everyone starts.

26
00:01:11,065 --> 00:01:13,747
You've got a brokerage account, a Reddit thread,

27
00:01:13,747 --> 00:01:17,810
maybe a TikTok algorithm feeding you stock tips between cat videos.

28
00:01:17,810 --> 00:01:20,403
You buy something because it went up recently.

29
00:01:20,403 --> 00:01:22,938
You sell it because it went down and scared you.

30
00:01:22,938 --> 00:01:23,833
That's it.

31
00:01:23,833 --> 00:01:25,932
That's the entire strategy.

32
00:01:25,932 --> 00:01:27,304
There's no thesis.

33
00:01:27,304 --> 00:01:28,424
No framework.

34
00:01:28,424 --> 00:01:31,505
Just vibes and hope dressed up as conviction.

35
00:01:31,505 --> 00:01:34,408
The Level 1 trader thinks they're investing.

36
00:01:34,408 --> 00:01:35,192
They're not.

37
00:01:35,192 --> 00:01:37,745
They're gambling with extra steps.

38
00:01:37,745 --> 00:01:42,587
And the dangerous part isn't even losing money — it's when you make money early.

39
00:01:42,587 --> 00:01:46,316
A beginner's luck win at Level 1 is one of the most financially

40
00:01:46,316 --> 00:01:49,008
destructive things that can happen to a person.

41
00:01:49,008 --> 00:01:52,417
Because now you have evidence that you're good at this.

42
00:01:52,417 --> 00:01:53,517
You're not.

43
00:01:53,517 --> 00:01:56,136
You got lucky in a rising market.

44
00:01:56,136 --> 00:01:59,847
Every Level 1 trader eventually learns this lesson.

45
00:02:00,564 --> 00:02:04,599
The only variable is how expensive the tuition is.

46
00:02:04,599 --> 00:02:06,520
The tell-tale sign you're here?

47
00:02:06,520 --> 00:02:10,295
You check your portfolio more than twice a day and you feel

48
00:02:10,295 --> 00:02:13,259
physically anxious when it's red.
